messages.textToSpeech:
You are now able to get your results by phone, text or my eHealth.

â€ŽThe time until test results are available may vary depending on testing location. Throughout B.C., there are many labs running tests seven days a week to get test results back as soon as possible.

The BCCDC COVID-19 Negative Results line (1-833-707-2792) is open from 8:30 AM to 4:30 PM, seven days a week. It may be easier to get through to someone on the line in the afternoon when the call volume is generally lower.

If you live in the Island Health Region, you can call the Laboratory Call Centre toll-free at 1-866-370-8355. The call centre is open Monday to Friday 7:00 AM to 6 PM and weekends (Saturday, Sunday) from 8:00 AM to 4:00 PM.

If you live in the Interior Health Region, you can check your results online on My Health Portal. My Health Portal support is available Monday to Friday, 7 a.m. to 7 p.m. (PST). For login assistance or for information on how to get access to the portal, call 1-844-870-4756.

Please note that the time until test results are available may vary depending on testing location.

If someone tests positive, public health will contact them. However, while you wait for your test result, you should follow the advice of your doctor or testing provider to self-isolate.

For access to the form to request your results by text or via the my eHealth please refer to Test Results.
